Short Description
At SPREAD, we empower great companies with great digital solutions!  
Our Platform optimizes engineering and product lifecycle processes, helping companies in the automotive, machinery, and defense sectors innovate while maintaining a focus on efficiency.
In this role, you’ll be a part of a highly skilled DevOps team that works cross-functionally with Engineering, Value Management, and Application Management teams. The balance between customer-facing responsibilities and internal infrastructure improvements makes this a dynamic and impactful position.
Your contributions will support smooth and efficient software operations and empower our clients to achieve greater efficiency and sustainability in their processes.
Your Mission

Deploy and set up new development tools and infrastructure for customer environments;
Work closely with customers to understand and address their unique technical setups, ensuring smooth deployments;
Collaborate with internal teams to automate and enhance development and release processes for both internal and external environments;
Test and review code, providing insights and feedback to optimize performance and resolve issues;
Troubleshoot technical problems, develop software updates, and implement fixes;
Contribute to project planning, providing insights into the technical aspects of deployments and infrastructure;
Establish and maintain monitoring and reporting processes to ensure smooth operation in both customer and in-house environments;
Foster a robust DevOps culture, promoting best practices and collaboration across the organization.

Your Experience
Must-Haves: 

5+ years of professional experience as a DevOps engineer or similar role;
Customer-facing experience, particularly in deploying software to cloud environments like AWS, Azure, or GCP.
Expertise in Kubernetes and Terraform, with experience in managing hybrid and multi-cloud setups;
Proficient in programming and scripting languages like Python and Bash;
Solid experience with distributed systems, CI/CD pipelines, monitoring, and alerting systems;
Strong understanding of database management (SQL/NoSQL), backups, restores, and migrations;
Deep knowledge of Linux systems, networking, security, and version control;
Ability to work autonomously in fast-paced, evolving environments, with an entrepreneurial and self-driven mindset;
Excellent spoken and written English skills.

Nice-to-Haves:

Experience with programming languages such as Golang, Rust, C++, or Typescript;
Familiarity with OpenShift;
Experience implementing high-availability, fault-tolerant solutions;
Strong communication and customer service skills, with the ability to explain complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Why us?

Amazing team
Our people are our most valuable asset. Work with over 100+ SPREADsters from 30+ different countries. Our team and our culture help us innovate and collaborate better every day.
High growth
Join a fast-growing, Series A-funded company with a steadily increasing ARR. Our customers love our revolutionary product, and we focus on their long-term success through genuine partnerships. We will nurture your unique skills and partner with exceptional peers to grow through experiences and collaboration.
High reward
Receive a competitive salary, virtual shares, and a flexible work setup. Enjoy 30 days of paid leave and many other perks to support your work-life harmony.
Continuous learning
Benefit from continuous learning opportunities with our dedicated budget and learning hubs, helping you develop your skills and stay ahead in your career.
Empowered ownership
Enjoy a culture of trust and transparency. With our ‘pull’ organization ethos, you’ll thrive in an environment that values collaboration and autonomy.
Outcome-oriented
We prioritize results over processes, embracing change and encouraging smart work. You’ll be encouraged to question the status quo and contribute to innovative solutions.
Diversity, equity, & inclusion
We celebrate diversity and create an inclusive environment where everyone's unique perspectives are valued.

